HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 136
BY REPRESENTATIVE HILFERTY
A RESOLUTION
To commend Al Petrie for his service to the Lakeview Civic Improvement Association.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Al Petrie for his incredible civic-
mindedness and to commend him for his service to the Lakeview Civic Improvement
Association; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Petrie is a past president of the Lakeview Civic Improvement
Association and the president and co-founder of Friends of Lakeview; in these roles, he has
united citizens with the aim of strengthening the Lakeview neighborhood in New Orleans,
Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, following Hurricane Katrina, Mr. Petrie led efforts to restore
Lakeview's green spaces to areas where families can gather, children can play, and neighbors
can reconnect with one another; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Petrie provided a vision for rebuilding and dedicated his energy to
rejuvenating Lakeview; he is a cofounder of the New Basin Canal Park restoration and
beautification project, which involved the installation of sidewalks, lanterns, and trees; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Petrie continues to serve Lakeview and demonstrates community
pride and resilience for the area's residents; he is truly most deserving of the highest
recognition for his outstanding efforts.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Al Petrie for his service to the Lakeview
Civic Improvement Association and does hereby extend sincere wishes that he remain
prosperous in his endeavors to serve his community.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
